From 4a5c76a5bb0092ce37537f9ac41bebe9cb21510f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 14 Jul 2025 16:12:16 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: PROTOCOL: wifi: ath12k:Support parsing and storage
 of both PSD and EIRP elements from TPE IE for composite APs

Add 'tpe_psd', 'tpe_eirp', 'num_tpe_psd', and 'num_tpe_eirp' fields to
'ath12k_reg_tpc_power_info' to store parsed PSD and EIRP values
from the TPE IE of the root AP. These values are used to populate the
WMI TPC command sent to firmware.
Remove the 'tpe' member from 'reg_tpc_info', as a single array cannot
represent both PSD and EIRP elements.
Replace all instances of 'reg_tpc_info->tpe' with either tpe_psd
or tpe_eirp based on the power type being handled.
Replace usage of 'reg_tpc_info->num_pwr_levels' with 'num_tpe_psd' or
'num_tpe_eirp' depending on whether PSD or EIRP values are being processed.
This change reflects the updated logic where both
PSD and EIRP values are parsed and stored separately.

Update 'ath12k_mac_parse_tx_pwr_env()' to parse and store
additional TPE PSD and EIRP values sent by composite APs.
This logic was missed during the package rebase and is now
added to ensure proper handling of composite APs.

Parse and store TPE PSD/EIRP values only if the root AP operates
in Standard Power mode and the station has not completed AFC.
For LPI and other power modes, parsing is not required as the
regulatory power is fixed.

Add a callback in ath12k_mac_bss_info_changed() to dynamically
re-parse TPE contents whenever the root AP’s beacon updates its TPE IE.
On detecting changes, re-parse the TPE and send an updated
WMI TPC command to firmware.

This change ensures compliance with 11be CTL requirements
by enabling the driver to transmit both PSD and EIRP limits for
SP power mode, and improves robustness in handling
dynamic TPE updates from composite APs.

